{
  "texts": [
    "Secondly, in education law, revising or interpreting educational legislation to formally integrate \"AI literacy\" and \"digital skills\" within the scope of the \"right to education\" is advisable.",
    "Educational laws should explicitly incorporate \"understanding and applying generative AI\" into defined educational objectives.",
    "For general adult education and lifelong learning frameworks, community colleges, vocational training centers, and online platforms should be encouraged to provide AI literacy programs, ensuring ongoing learning opportunities across individuals' life stages.",
    "For example, California's recent law requiring schools to teach students about AI signifies a growing recognition of the importance of equipping young people with these essential skills (Jones 2024).",
    "Furthermore, legislation governing educational facilities should include broadband networks, smart terminal devices, and cloud computing resources as essential educational infrastructure, clarifying spending proportions or minimum standards in terms of network coverage rates and per capita device ownership."
  ]
}